{"type":"message","id":"ea919713","parentId":"ef181b1f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:39:36.827Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_z8ilc45gtn69_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5132\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=723\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation proposed] a\r\n[master 0acfad1] pulse: 2026-03-24 003814\n 7 files changed, 327 insertions(+), 150 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 003814.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 003814.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 003637.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 003814 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires analyzing pulse log files to classify invariant vs variant content. I need to first understand the structure of existing pulse logs to build an effective classifier.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"marine-lobster","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5132\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=723\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation proposed] a\r\n[master 0acfad1] pulse: 2026-03-24 003814\n 7 files changed, 327 insertions(+), 150 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 003814.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 003814.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 003637.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 003814 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires analyzing pulse log files to classify invariant vs variant content. I need to first understand the structure of existing pulse logs to build an effective classifier.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774327176822}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b172313","parentId":"ea919713","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:39:36.831Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_z8ilc45gtn69_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 003637\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: tic_experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. The big insight is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n3. The next action is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression):\r\n   - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n   - Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n   - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe pending tasks include:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n- Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n- Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nGiven the current insight about compression-causal duality, the most logical next action would be to start implementing the TIC classifier experiment. Let me look at what's available:\r\n\r\n1. I need to implement the TIC classifier\r\n2. I should use the pulse logs in `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n3. The hypothesis is that causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action. The most focused action would be to:\r\n1. Create the TIC experiment script/code that will analyze the pulse logs\r\n2. Or create a document outlining the TIC implementation approach\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pattern, the best single action would be to create the TIC classifier implementation. Let me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant vs variant patterns\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me first check what pulse logs exist and their structure to make an informed implementation.\r\n\r\nActually, I should just take a concrete action. The most impactful single action would be to create the TIC classifier script that implements the experiment described in the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY document.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll craft a precise Python implementation to test the TIC classifier's core hypothesis, focusing on extracting structural invariants from pulse logs and measuring their predictive power.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the logical next step for Phase 1 advancement, requiring a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script that reads pulse logs, identifies structural invariants, and attempts to predict next-pulse content - establishing the baseline for the >70% classification and >60% prediction success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\n\r\n## Purpose\r\nTest hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure. Compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Input\r\n- Pulse logs from `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n- Sequence: pulse_N → pulse_(N+1)\r\n\r\n### Classifier: Invariant vs Variant Detection\r\n\r\n**Invariant Categories (stable across pulses):**\r\n1. Goal hierarchy (Active, Pending, Completed)\r\n2. File paths referenced\r\n3. Agent identity (Breakaway/MiniMax-M2.7)\r\n4. Structural patterns (OBSERVATION/ACTION/MUTATION blocks)\r\n\r\n**Variant Categories (changes between pulses):**\r\n1. Timestamps\r\n2. Specific file edits\r\n3. Observed state changes\r\n4. Pending/completed items\r\n\r\n### Prediction Task\r\nGiven pulse_N invariants → predict pulse_(N+1) content\r\n\r\n### Success Criteria\r\n- Classification accuracy: >70% invariant/variant\r\n- Prediction accuracy: >60% next-pulse content\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\n# Invariant patterns (should persist across sessions)\r\nINVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"# CURRENT GOALS\",\r\n    r\"## Active\",\r\n    r\"## Completed\",\r\n    r\"## Pending\",\r\n    r\"### OBSERVATION\",\r\n    r\"### ACTION\",\r\n    r\"### MUTATION\",\r\n    r\"file:\",  # file: line in MUTATION blocks\r\n    r\"Breakaway\",\r\n    r\"stateless\",\r\n    r\"discontinuous\",\r\n]\r\n\r\n# Variant patterns (expected to change)\r\nVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\",  # dates\r\n    r\"\\d{6}\",  # timestamps\r\n    r\"old_text:\",\r\n    r\"new_text:\",\r\n    r\"```\\n.*?\\n```\",  # code blocks\r\n]\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(content: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structural invariants from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n    invariants = set()\r\n    for pattern in INVARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        if re.search(pattern, content):\r\n            invariants.add(pattern)\r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef extract_variants(content: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract content that varies between pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    variants = set()\r\n    for pattern in VARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n        matches = re.findall(pattern, content)\r\n        variants.update(matches)\r\n    return variants\r\n\r\ndef classify_pulse(content: str) -> Dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse content into invariant/variant.\"\"\"\r\n    return {\r\n        \"invariants\": extract_invariants(content),\r\n        \"variants\": extract_variants(content),\r\n        \"invariant_count\": len(extract_invariants(content)),\r\n        \"variant_count\": len(extract_variants(content)),\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants: set) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content from invariants\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:37:03\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774327176826}}
